OL,3,CDozens dead in France as 'heat dome'
OL,4,Cbrings 40C temperatures to Europe
OL,6,FAt least 42 people have died and more
OL,7,Fthan 800 schools have closed in France
OL,8,Fas Europe struggles with scorching
OL,9,Ftemperatures of more than 40C.
OL,11,FSpeaking after a crisis meeting on
OL,12,FMonday, French Prime Minister
OL,13,FSebastien Lecornu said that 40 of the
OL,14,Fdeaths were due to drowning and
OL,15,Fhappened in the last five days. Many
OL,16,Fof the victims were young people, he
OL,17,Fadded.
OL,26,@uD@Brr
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
