FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1782290901
OL,3,CDozens dead in France as 'heat dome'
OL,4,Cbrings 40C temperatures to Europe
OL,6,FOfficials in southeastern France also
OL,7,Fsaid the heatwave was the most likely
OL,8,Freason for the additional deaths of
OL,9,Ftwo children, aged two and four, who
OL,10,Fwere found unconscious in a car
OL,11,Foutside their home in Carpentras.
OL,13,FA manslaughter inquiry has since been
OL,14,Flaunched after a police source told
OL,15,Fthe French newspaper Le Parisien that
OL,16,Fthe mother said she had "forgotten her
OL,17,Fchildren" in the car while shopping.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1782290901
OL,3,CDozens dead in France as 'heat dome'
OL,4,Cbrings 40C temperatures to Europe
OL,6,FThe deaths come as France's
OL,7,Fmeteorological service, Meteo France,
OL,8,Fplaced 54 departments ` or
OL,9,Fadministrative regions ` under a red
OL,10,Fheat alert, with Bordeaux hitting 42C
OL,11,Fon Monday.
OL,13,FSebastien Leas, forecaster for Meteo
OL,14,FFrance, said: "The coming days are
OL,15,Fshaping up to be among the ten hottest
OL,16,Fever recorded nationwide.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1782290901
OL,3,CDozens dead in France as 'heat dome'
OL,4,Cbrings 40C temperatures to Europe
OL,6,F"So it's not only the intensity of
OL,7,Fthis heatwave that is exceptional, but
OL,8,Falso how early it is, since it began
OL,9,Feven before the official start of
OL,10,Fsummer and will apparently continue
OL,11,Funtil the end of the week."
OL,13,FRed heat alerts have been issued
OL,14,Facross Europe, in the UK, Italy,
OL,15,FFrance and Spain, while Belgium,
OL,16,FGermany, and Portugal will also see
OL,17,Ftemperatures in the high 30Cs this
OL,18,Fweek.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1782290901
OL,3,CDozens dead in France as 'heat dome'
OL,4,Cbrings 40C temperatures to Europe
OL,6,FThe French government prohibited the
OL,7,Fsale of alcohol at events, including
OL,8,Fthe popular festival, Fete de la
OL,9,FMusique, and also said it would close
OL,10,Fthe Eiffel Tower early on Tuesday due
OL,11,Fto the heatwave.
OL,13,FPresident Emmanuel Macron has urged
OL,14,Fthe public to drink plenty of water
OL,15,Fand look after the elderly, children,
OL,16,Fand isolated people.
OL,18,FFrench Education Minister Edouard
OL,19,FGeffray said on Monday that more than
OL,20,F800 schools had closed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
